  <h2>The Discipline is:</h2>
  <p>an <span class="def" id="expulsion">expulsion*</span>.</p>
</div>
  <h2>Response:</h2>
  <p>School administrators must give you written notification of  the intent to expel your child. In the case of a proposed expulsion, you are  entitled to written notice that contains a complete statement of the facts, a  list of witnesses and a description of their testimony, as well as many other  procedural rights under the Minnesota Pupil Fair Dismissal Act.<sup class="statute">1</sup></p>
  <p>The IEP team, including you, along with school district  representatives must have a <span class="def" id="manifestation-determination">manifestation determination meeting*</span> as soon as  possible but no more than 10 school days after the decision to seek  an expulsion is made.<sup class="statute">2</sup></p>
  <p class="tip">Tip: The district must  provide alternative educational services to the extent a removal from educational services exceeds five consecutive school days. </p>
